        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} After we had packed the suitcases and stored at the bottom of the entrance, we made our way with the metro to Saint Hellen&rsquo;s Island. According to Google, there should be a little bit to see and Matze might want to take one or the other photo of one of the main bridges in Montreal. When we arrived on the platform, we found that there were no rails there and the metro drives here on normal wheels. After a few googling, Matze found that normal steel bikes could not overcome the necessary climbs that would have been necessary here in Montreal. We are also here in the French part of Canada and that's why solidarity ride the same tracks as Paris. "The Canadians again." </p>
        <p> When we arrived on the island, we found that there is not too much going on here today. Most footpaths were completely hidden under thick layers of ice. We only took a few photos and then we decided to make our way back. It had become pretty cold again overnight. Uncomfortably cold. </p>
        <p> Back in the city center we crept a little through the shopping centers, ate something and treat ourselves to a great dessert in a train station Caf&eacute;. </p>

