        <p> Then came the ordered taxi, which brought us to the airport. Once there, we found that we were there a lot too early and that the switch was not yet open. When we had to look at the ads, we were also informed that our flight was late. Great. Oh a hasth wait. How long do we have time in London for changing? Only 1.5 hours ups then we have a little problem now. </p>
        <p> As soon as the switch opened, we were already facing an extremely helpful lady who gave everything to help both of us. She informed us that we would not reach the plane in London and that is why British Airways had already resold our two seats. The next flight from London to Hamburg, with free seats, would only have been 10 hours later. Really now? The friendly lady really gave everything. She tried many other variants and also to bring us to Germany with other airlines. In the end, she had a solution that at first glance didn't sound so stupid. She booked us on a flight from Montreal to Paris with Air France. From there it should continue to Hamburg after a short stay. We would then have landed only with a delay of just over 1 hour in Hamburg. Of course, we asked here for a free upgrade. Unfortunately we were not lucky today and had to fly wood class. </p>
