        <p> Matze was not pleased when he squeezed into the narrow gang. At least the square next to him was free. The film selection on this 7 -hour flight was also not to be used and I don't even want to start eating. We both actually thought that the French like good food. Unfortunately, it was not noticeable up here. </p>
        <p> Arrived in Paris, Matze almost beaten up with a lady from the security service when she started pulling very rough Matze's expensive camera equipment from his backpack. When we finally arrived at the gate through passport control and some crowds, there was a delay there again. The moment we were supposed to fly, the plane was just rolling up to the gate. Matze definitely has the snout from the French. Very full! </p>
        <p> In Hamburg, a rental car was waiting for Matze again. Unfortunately, a warning lamp shone when you start. So swap back to the switch and car again. Of course everything was not a problem and ran smoothly here too, but it took a further time. </p>
        <p> We should actually arrive in Hamburg at noon. When we drove off with the rental car, the sun was already hung very deep above the city. </p>
